rComments: Although the lectures are dull and the prof is a little deadpan, this class is very simple to understand since some concepts are what you have already learnt in the past few years. The grading is fair and lenient. All you need to do to do well are finding a reliable team and practicing past questions. Very suitable to choose as an elective.

This prof knows the truth about the modern education, which teaches you nothing, so she will provide many resources to ensure high grades for you. Very realistic way of teaching. I have seen many bad profs at Telfer who neither teach nor give high grades. You will not regret taking this class because it is a boost to your GPA!

I gave her a 5/5 review after ADM3350. Unfortunately, ADM4352 is a disaster with no actual teaching and no clear grading criteria. From what I've heard from classmates, you'd be better off taking one of the other 4th year finance courses.

Very organised prof who gives you a lot of resources to achieve success in the class. The group formation is quite painful but you will benefit a lot if your teammates are competent. A lot of examples are included in the class, so you will not drown when it comes to the exams.

Professor Lajili really demonstrates what it means to accommodate in online learning environment. She creates convenience for students by posting MCQs and practice problems, which is highly similar to the exams. Go to her lectures and pay attention to the announcements. A true gem at Telfer.

She is probably one of the worst profs at uOttawa. I don't mean by personality like the hot head gordon lenjosek but her teaching abilities. Finance should be as interactive with mathematics as it is with theory and she teaches little to no math related questions. She expects you to know all equations from previous classes lol. What a load of bs.

Her lectures might be boring and confusing, but the practice problems and practice quizzes she posts on Brightspace help a lot if you want to do well in assignments and exams. She is also willing to answer students' questions, and all you need to do is to go to her office hours on MS team to express your questions to her. Strongly recommend.
Group assignments are very easy, midterm has no surprises since she provides lots of practice exercises and past midterms that are very similar. I would definitely recommend this prof for ADM3350.

Lajili is a pretty great prof and I would definitely take her again. Between reading the book and going to her lectures you'll be fine. My only criticism is that she is not at all helpful via email. Even for a quick question, you'll have to visit her during office hours. We had two group assignments (easy), a midterm and final.

I would recommend her! She will post everything you need for enough practice on brightspace this includes old exams, practice problems and MCQ. There is absolutely no surprises in the midterm or final. She will reuse the same questions posted online. She is a great professor and I would take her again.
Good professor. Teaches you how to apply topics to the real world. Doesn't go over that many formulas though. Is willing to address questions after class and outside of class.
She is willing to help if you don't understand the material. All that you need is in the notes that she posted. The midterm and final are the same as the assignments.
Uses the same examples from her homework assignments and past midterms and final exams. If you study those and know how to do them you're golden

Professor Lajili has no clear grading rubric. She assigns you a grade based on her personal opinion and is not fair when comparing groups. When asking for reasons behind marks, she comes up with unclear feedback. Honestly, don't even take the class if she is teaching it even if the material seems interesting. I regret taking her class.

Professor Lajili is one of the best finance profs I've had so far. She makes class interesting by integrating videos and current discussion topics and provides lots of practice problems (which are almost identical to exam questions). Definitely sparked an interest for corporate finance in me!

Go to class if you want to learn how the subject applies to the real world. Doesn't really teach the material in class very much. Read the slides and book. If you can do the exercise questions youre golden. Reuses assignment questions and midterms.
If you pay attention in class and know the material reasonably well, you'll do fine in the course. Is very helpful if you need extra help on the homework sets.
Insanely boring and terrible at teaching the course content.

A very nice professor who uses case studies and real-world business problems to challenge her students.  Classes are interactive with lots of presentations, but the material is never dry.  She holds her students to a high-standard, as she should, this class being the cap-stone course for the finance specialization.  Very good professor.

I actually liked this prof. She talked about random stuff and watched pointless videos but her exams were exactly what she said and were pretty easy. Might not be an amazing lecturer but she was fair.

Terrible prof. Skips slides and quickly reads some aloud. Provides useless paraphrased explanations. Asks class what the answers are to problems. When no one knows she'll ask another 3 times, until someone guesses wrong. Only shows the work, never does it. Watch lots of useless videos that are never tested. Brutal with tech. Reuses assign Qs. Avoid

Very nice professor, reuses assignment questions from year to year and on exams all the questions have been from either assignments or class problems. Overall pretty easy class and some interesting material if you are interested in finance.
Exams are exactly the problems covered in class

This is seriously one of the worst profs I've ever had. She never ever responds to emails and she'd rather call out people in class than teach. She kept the same assignments and midterms but when it came to the final she gave us something we never saw in class. Thanks for ruining my specialization in finance

Worst teacher at the university. Can't convey the material at all, expects you to know everything already. No problems to practice with, uses her laser pointer to point at students. Whines and complains the entire class while boring students to death. She should have picked another career path. AVOID AT ALL COST.

please dont expect to understand the material in her class. She is not willing to help students at all(she didnt answer my questions)She wants to end 3 hour class in 2 hours.I'm not happy that I took the course with her.NOT CLEAR AT ALL
She is terrible!  Boring, and boring, and did I say boring?  She does not care about her students.  She has absolutely no passion.

She is a very nice ladt and really willing to help if you dont understand a topic. The inclass examples get tedious, but pay attention cause she uses very similiar questions on tests...if you have a choice between her and Prof Ryan...choose her!
Horrible teacher, you could go in knowing your stuff insdie out, and she'd find a way to confuse you. Find another prof!

Though she has an accent, which makes her kinda hard to follow, she's a real sweetheart and a good teacher. She's very understanding (some students take advantage of that) and does her absolute best to help you in her class.
Aweful...She can't even speak english very well...looks like she wants to be elsewhere. Avoid....the class all about the zzzzz'n
